"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## How Thoreau improved my vision\\n\\n[![Eric Weiner](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/2\\\\*lyhdcq0OSUfLCxmCQpr2TQ.jpeg)](https://ericweiner.medium.com/?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://ericweiner.medium.com/?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Eric Weiner](https://ericweiner.medium.com/?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://forge.medium.com/the-art-of-seeing-32fd0a4fd1ca?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[4 days ago·5 min read](https://forge.medium.com/the-art-of-seeing-32fd0a4fd1ca?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*68Iw4nlMi69ug\\\\_8M)\\n\\nPhoto by [Harry Quan](https://unsplash.com/@mango_quan?utm_source=medium\\\\&utm_medium=referral) on [Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=medium\\\\&utm_medium=referral)\\n\\nI thought my vision was pretty good. Not quite 20–20, but close. Then I read Thoreau.\\n\\nYes, *that *Thoreau. Forget what you may have read by or about the “hermit Concord.” He is misunderstood. His experiment on Walden Pond was about seeing. All the rest — the solitude, the simplicity — were means to this end.\\n\",\"timestamp\":1640455656,\"title\":\"The Art of Seeing - Forge\"},\"digest\":\"0kb7AQ5g8Wrh0v8Xf3jtTD0TQpUey9HvrTuGF30Bhg8\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x6d89392FCCa12DdF31B884434237e37A5d1d7686\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"ifDMP5rxv6knH51P-0ArX1_IHn5bR06-Ell9MfmBtRQ\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"uyzaHtJLh6xkOjPklIr9suqezdMbd_jGa3bo-40cvXI\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"vpUMBM9mj3uIxpYyRePAZlRj98bRTUeUG-CK8sFEcec1asI8VccyIFxiGWBZvQahsCLmAA5WTUxi9Xqg7ixcJg\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x50e11c57ba41c0f9bb9e6aea5059bde179e184f4cd5812ba2da4b6ab816593ef3ee2a2